{"data":{"post":{"id":"c289b941-402b-5c0e-b618-1d74dadcc298","html":"<p><strong>“How many corrugated cardboards did <a href=\"http://www.pistoletto.it/\" title=\"Michelangelo Pistoletto\">Michelangelo Pistoletto</a> use for this show?”</strong> I asked one of the invigilators at the <a href=\"http://www.serpentinegallery.org\" title=\"serpentine\">Serpentine Gallery</a> when I visited there last week. “I don’t know,” she said, surprised at the incredulity of my question while giving me a look that says “Does it really matter?” She was right – it really didn’t matter <strong>because the effect is a labyrinth and experience of space like nothing else you can imagine.</strong></p>\n<p>Except the space for the <strong>Mirror of Judgement</strong> is made out of rolls and rolls of corrugated cardboard, a cheap material that is accessible and familiar in our consciousness. As one of the early pioneers of <strong>Arte Povera</strong> or “Poor Art”, <strong>Michelangelo Pistoletto</strong> has explored the use of cheap  materials to seek fundamental discussions on contemporary life.</p>\n<p>\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n  \n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/momardi/static/f8dfbe8226e12ebbb7fc7156354bd35d/33e24/michelangelo_pistoletto_1_rndhlk.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 480px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 149.375%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"michelangelo pistoletto 1 rndhlk\"\n        title=\"Michelangelo Pistoletto: The Labyrinth 1969-2007. Corrugated cardboard. Meters of cardboard. Courtesy Galleria Continua, San Gimignano / Beijing / Le Moulin. Photo by Oak Taylor-Smith. © 2011 Michelangelo Pistoletto\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/f8dfbe8226e12ebbb7fc7156354bd35d/33e24/michelangelo_pistoletto_1_rndhlk.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/f8dfbe8226e12ebbb7fc7156354bd35d/7084e/michelangelo_pistoletto_1_rndhlk.jpg 200w,\n/momardi/static/f8dfbe8226e12ebbb7fc7156354bd35d/e263b/michelangelo_pistoletto_1_rndhlk.jpg 400w,\n/momardi/static/f8dfbe8226e12ebbb7fc7156354bd35d/33e24/michelangelo_pistoletto_1_rndhlk.jpg 480w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 480px) 100vw, 480px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n  <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Michelangelo Pistoletto: The Labyrinth 1969-2007. Corrugated cardboard. Meters of cardboard. Courtesy Galleria Continua, San Gimignano / Beijing / Le Moulin. Photo by Oak Taylor-Smith. © 2011 Michelangelo Pistoletto</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n      </p>\n<p>\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n  \n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/momardi/static/dd027eda77085d30ca0a05e58dcb4331/55fd7/michelangelo_pistoletto_2_atuxvj.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 640px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 68.28125%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"michelangelo pistoletto 2 atuxvj\"\n        title=\"Michelangelo Pistoletto: Installation view, Serpentine Gallery, London (12 July – 17 September 2011 © 2011 Sebastiano Pellion)\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/dd027eda77085d30ca0a05e58dcb4331/55fd7/michelangelo_pistoletto_2_atuxvj.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/dd027eda77085d30ca0a05e58dcb4331/e81c0/michelangelo_pistoletto_2_atuxvj.jpg 200w,\n/momardi/static/dd027eda77085d30ca0a05e58dcb4331/8e8ea/michelangelo_pistoletto_2_atuxvj.jpg 400w,\n/momardi/static/dd027eda77085d30ca0a05e58dcb4331/55fd7/michelangelo_pistoletto_2_atuxvj.jpg 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n  <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Michelangelo Pistoletto: Installation view, Serpentine Gallery, London (12 July – 17 September 2011 © 2011 Sebastiano Pellion)</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n      </p>\n<p>Here, Michelangelo stretches the normal limitations of cardboard, highlighting it not only <strong>as the central figure in the show, but also creating it as the architecture within the architecture.</strong> It has transformed the Serpentine gallery as a living, breathing and intimate space.</p>\n<p>Apart from rolls and rolls and winding maze of cardboard, there are large-scale mirrors that welcome the visitor when they arrive at specific corners of sacred space that pay homage to different religions. <strong>There is a prayer mat, a life-size Buddha, a Gothic prayer-kneeler</strong> in front of these mirrors which  invite the viewer to explore their reflection as well contemplate on deeper religious truths, or perhaps the labyrinth of life itself.</p>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\"\n            style=\"padding-bottom: 78.90625%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;margin-bottom: 2em\"\n          >\n            <iframe allowfullscreen class=\"youtube-player\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/AoxzUuy4QRo?wmode=transparent&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;iv_load_policy=3&amp;showsearch=0&amp;rel=0&amp;theme=dark\" title=\"YouTube video player\" type=\"text/html\" style=\"\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          \"></iframe>\n          </div>\n          </div>\n<figcaption>Michelangelo Pistoletto explains the meaning of Mirror of Judgement</figcaption>\n<p>\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n  \n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/momardi/static/a2d5e17609b739eaeee7db6d582f6093/33e24/michelangelo_pistoletto_4_lbu0tx.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 480px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 143.125%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"michelangelo pistoletto 4 lbu0tx\"\n        title=\"Michelangelo Pistoletto. Installation view, Serpentine Gallery, London. (12 July – 17 September 2011) © 2011 Sebastiano Pellion\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/a2d5e17609b739eaeee7db6d582f6093/33e24/michelangelo_pistoletto_4_lbu0tx.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/a2d5e17609b739eaeee7db6d582f6093/7084e/michelangelo_pistoletto_4_lbu0tx.jpg 200w,\n/momardi/static/a2d5e17609b739eaeee7db6d582f6093/e263b/michelangelo_pistoletto_4_lbu0tx.jpg 400w,\n/momardi/static/a2d5e17609b739eaeee7db6d582f6093/33e24/michelangelo_pistoletto_4_lbu0tx.jpg 480w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 480px) 100vw, 480px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n  <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Michelangelo Pistoletto. Installation view, Serpentine Gallery, London. (12 July – 17 September 2011) © 2011 Sebastiano Pellion</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n      </p>\n<p>I found myself gazing at my own self several times, contemplating my place not just as a viewer but as a participant of the installation, <strong>discovering that each angle I took reveals a new nook, a new corner, a new perspective.</strong></p>\n<p>And perhaps that is the real success of this show - <strong>it allows the viewer to seek his or her place within the installation and find personal meanings</strong>. Michelangelo cares about what we think and elevates our position to part-creator in the whole experience of seeing, viewing, interacting. In fact, I imagine Michelangelo watching us from a screen, amused with our reactions as we walk thru the winding maze of cardboard labyrinth at the Serpentine.</p>\n<p>\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n  \n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/momardi/static/0eb2f1c59a894be846aa49db549dfda5/33e24/michelangelo_pistolett_3_z0c0hc.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 480px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 150%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"michelangelo pistolett 3 z0c0hc\"\n        title=\"Michelangelo Pistoletto: Installation view, Serpentine Gallery, London (12 July – 17 September 2011) © 2011 Sebastiano Pellion\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/0eb2f1c59a894be846aa49db549dfda5/33e24/michelangelo_pistolett_3_z0c0hc.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/0eb2f1c59a894be846aa49db549dfda5/7084e/michelangelo_pistolett_3_z0c0hc.jpg 200w,\n/momardi/static/0eb2f1c59a894be846aa49db549dfda5/e263b/michelangelo_pistolett_3_z0c0hc.jpg 400w,\n/momardi/static/0eb2f1c59a894be846aa49db549dfda5/33e24/michelangelo_pistolett_3_z0c0hc.jpg 480w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 480px) 100vw, 480px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n  <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Michelangelo Pistoletto: Installation view, Serpentine Gallery, London (12 July – 17 September 2011) © 2011 Sebastiano Pellion</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n      </p>\n<p>The beauty of Mirror of Judgment is that is as you go thru the whole gallery, you still wonder what you might discover or imagine. On a personal note, my experience was very spiritual. <strong>Mirror of Judgment</strong> helped me obtain a new idea of myself – that I could be so much more than just an insignificant viewer of artworks. That I could be a part of an artwork as a co-creator by simply breathing it, living it and being on it.</p>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\"\n            style=\"padding-bottom: 78.90625%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;margin-bottom: 2em\"\n          >\n            <iframe allowfullscreen class=\"youtube-player\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/aW1Ebxz7hZs?wmode=transparent&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;iv_load_policy=3&amp;showsearch=0&amp;rel=0&amp;theme=dark&amp;feature=related\" title=\"YouTube video player\" type=\"text/html\" style=\"\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          \"></iframe>\n          </div>\n          </div>\n<figcaption>The experience</figcaption>\n<p>Related Links:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/art/reviews/michelangelo-pistoletto-serpentine-gallery-london-2319356.html\" title=\"Charles Darwent, Independent: michelangelo\">Michelangelo Pistoletto, Serpentine Gallery by Charles Darwent for the Independent</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/artanddesign/jonathanjonesblog/2011/jul/12/michelangelo-pistoletto-stunning-reflections\" title=\"Jonathan Jones: Michelangelo Pistoletto\">Michelangelo Pistoletto’s stunning reflections from Jonathan Jones for the Guardian</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/artanddesign/2011/jul/24/michelangelo-pistoletto-mirror-judgement-review\" title=\"Laura Cummings on Michelangelo Pistoletto\">Michelangelo Pistoletto: The Mirror of Judgment by Laura Cummings for the Guardian</a></li>\n</ul>","fields":{"slug":"/last-twodays-mirror-of-judgement-michelangelo-pistoletto-at-the-serpentine-gallery/","prefix":"2011-09-15"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Last Two Days of Mirror of Judgement: Michelangelo Pistoletto at the Serpentine Gallery","category":"exhibits","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/momardi/static/dd027eda77085d30ca0a05e58dcb4331/d927d/michelangelo_pistoletto_2_atuxvj.jpg"}}}}},"authornote":{"id":"b6415c02-57f6-5889-8910-a05deb06efca","html":"<p>Article by <strong>Tuesday Gutierrez</strong>. Former digital marketing manager for the London 2012 Festival, the largest UK festival ever staged. This is her blog about contemporary art, design, film, photography and all that move her soul.</p>"}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/last-twodays-mirror-of-judgement-michelangelo-pistoletto-at-the-serpentine-gallery/","prev":{"id":"2bb886d6-e421-55d2-b6a6-0e894db09d75","fields":{"slug":